1
00:00:35,785 --> 00:00:36,786
Sir.

2
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:39,039
-What?
-Nadeem escaped.

3
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:40,290
He's in the wind.

4
00:00:42,751 --> 00:00:43,960
Then find him!

5
00:01:04,647 --> 00:01:05,982
Hello, Wilson.

6
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:32,008
[Foggy] Okay. There's nobody watching.

7
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:43,478
[Matt] Straight up there, please.

8
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:46,606
Nice and easy. No rush.

9
00:01:47,357 --> 00:01:48,441
[Brett] Go.

10
00:01:53,988 --> 00:01:55,573
[Foggy] Thanks, Mrs. Mahoney.

11
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:58,201
[Mrs. Mahoney] Y'all ain't the only ones
haunted by Wilson Fisk.

12
00:02:00,078 --> 00:02:01,204
Thank you, dear.

13
00:02:03,873 --> 00:02:07,502
Uh, fresh sheets on the bed.
Towels if you need.

14
00:02:14,175 --> 00:02:16,302
Uh... Thank you. Really.

15
00:02:17,428 --> 00:02:19,722
And don't worry. Nobody knows you're here.

16
00:02:25,603 --> 00:02:26,521
Seema, if you--

17
00:02:26,604 --> 00:02:29,274
You promised
you would never lie to me again.

18
00:02:33,987 --> 00:02:35,947
Seems, if you understood
what was going on here--

19
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:38,241
Do you know why I married you, Ray?

20
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:43,163
It wasn't your good looks
or my father's blessing.

21
00:02:43,913 --> 00:02:48,209
It was because I believed in my soul that
I had found a good man who would love me.

22
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:51,254
And who would be
completely honest with me.

23
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:52,630
Seems, I do love you...

24
00:02:52,714 --> 00:02:55,717
You lied again and again.

25
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:59,179
And now here we are, running.

26
00:02:59,929 --> 00:03:01,723
Hiding in some lady's house.

27
00:03:01,806 --> 00:03:05,101
Fisk played me. Okay?
And before I knew it--

28
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:07,187
You brought a gunfight to our home!

29
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,524
You're right.

30
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:14,736
About everything.

31
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:20,116
But I will fix it.

32
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:26,664
Sami was curled up with me in a bathtub,
waiting for men to come kill him.

33
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:29,542
Do you know what I hoped for
in that moment?

34
00:03:29,626 --> 00:03:33,213
That they'd kill him first,
so he didn't have to watch me die.

35
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:35,256
How do you fix that?

36
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:37,759
Seems, Seems... [kissing hands]

37
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:41,346
I am so sorry.

38
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:47,018
But I will make you and Sami safe.

39
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:50,146
I promise you.

40
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:54,525
I can't let what you say
matter to me anymore, Rahul.

41
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:58,780
Sami deserves at least one person
in his life he can trust.

42
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:01,991
And that's never going to be you.

43
00:04:19,634 --> 00:04:22,887
Mahoney really stepped up for us.
Mrs. M, too.

44
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:24,806
Everyone in the neighborhood
wants Fisk gone.

45
00:04:24,889 --> 00:04:27,892
Foggy, you don't need
to talk me into this anymore.

46
00:04:27,976 --> 00:04:30,061
I promised we'd do it your way,
and we are.

47
00:04:30,144 --> 00:04:31,896
Good. 'Cause it's gonna work.

48
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,564
Good. I hope you're right.

49
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:36,025
[door opens]

50
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:38,653
Are we clear?

51
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:46,869
[sighs] So, what now?

52
00:04:47,704 --> 00:04:51,708
You're going to testify against Fisk,
once you hire us to represent you.

53
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:54,669
Represent me?

54
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:57,547
As Nelson and Murdock, attorneys at law.

55
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,802
[theme music playing] [classical music playing]

56
00:06:32,892 --> 00:06:35,853
Three restaurants,
the best spa in the city...

57
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:40,775
a full staff waiting
to fulfill our every need,

58
00:06:40,858 --> 00:06:41,984
It's all ours.

59
00:06:42,944 --> 00:06:43,945
"Ours"? You bought it?

60
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:46,823
For you.

61
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:50,660
There's a penthouse
with the best view of the city.

62
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,246
Our city.

63
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:57,125
[sighs]

64
00:06:58,334 --> 00:07:00,086
It's everything you've ever wanted.

65
00:07:04,715 --> 00:07:05,967
[soft droning]

66
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:09,303
[metal detector beeping]

67
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,982
-Sir, uh...
-Not now.

68
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:24,277
-It's important.
-Not now.

69
00:07:28,197 --> 00:07:29,031
[man] Good night.

70
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,658
[soft droning]

71
00:07:50,261 --> 00:07:51,721
Can I get you something?

72
00:07:52,930 --> 00:07:54,056
Champagne?

73
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:58,352
Not now, thank you.

74
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:13,117
I don't have your eye...

75
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:19,248
but I hung them
where I guessed you would like them.

76
00:08:20,082 --> 00:08:25,463
We can move them or...
buy other ones, whatever you like.

77
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:33,346
I thought that you might
want to curate a collection

78
00:08:33,429 --> 00:08:35,890
and display it throughout the hotel.

79
00:08:50,238 --> 00:08:51,280
Thank you.

80
00:08:52,114 --> 00:08:53,699
This is all so generous.

81
00:08:54,242 --> 00:08:57,036
It's nothing.
I wanted you to feel welcome.

82
00:08:57,119 --> 00:08:58,037
I do.

83
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:01,040
It's...

84
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:04,835
incredible.

85
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:08,965
Do you want something to eat
from one of the restaurants,

86
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:10,883
or I could make you something?

87
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:14,470
I'm not hungry... just tired.

88
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,056
I'm sorry.

89
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:19,976
You've gone through so much trouble.

90
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:21,394
No, no. Please. I...

91
00:09:22,311 --> 00:09:25,064
You had a long trip. I should have...

92
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:29,485
I should have realized
that this could be overwhelming.

93
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:30,945
It's sweet...

94
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:36,033
but all I want right now
is a hot bath and a soft bed.

95
00:09:39,912 --> 00:09:42,498
The master suite is upstairs.
I'll show you.

96
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:43,624
No need.

97
00:09:44,792 --> 00:09:45,835
I'll find it.

98
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:12,820
This is your law office?

99
00:10:12,903 --> 00:10:15,615
Nobody knows about this place.
We'll be safe here. Take a seat.

100
00:10:21,495 --> 00:10:22,872
Ms. Page. Agent Nadeem.

101
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:30,296
You tried to warn me about Fisk.

102
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:33,090
I should have listened.

103
00:10:34,258 --> 00:10:38,387
-And about what happened at the church--
-Let's not... Let's not go there.

104
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:40,765
In the end, you got me out alive,

105
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:43,142
so I guess that means
we're on the same side now.

106
00:10:45,102 --> 00:10:47,229
Yeah. I guess it does.

107
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:50,524
All right. We're gonna get your family
safe, Ray, but we can't ask for WITSEC.

108
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:53,444
If Fisk got to the Bureau,
he can get to the Marshals Service.

109
00:10:53,527 --> 00:10:57,531
We were thinking overseas.
Maybe with a friend or a distant relative.

110
00:10:57,615 --> 00:10:59,075
Uh...

111
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:01,911
my brother's wife has a cousin in Bihar.

112
00:11:01,994 --> 00:11:04,997
-I never liked him.
-[Karen] Oh, I can get 'em a flight.

113
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:06,916
But Fisk's people
will be watching the airports,

114
00:11:06,999 --> 00:11:08,459
so we should fly 'em out of Montreal.

115
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:15,383
Um, I've had some time to think
about how to get away from him.

116
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:18,386
[Ray] They'll be watching
my bank accounts.

117
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:19,428
We'll cover it.

118
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:25,184
Thanks.

119
00:11:26,727 --> 00:11:28,688
But it might be more than I deserve.

120
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:35,403
Look, you... you hurt people.

121
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:38,572
It doesn't have to define you.

122
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:43,911
You should get ready, Ray.

123
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:45,871
Locker room is through there.

124
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:49,458
Yeah.

125
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:02,930
You're right.
His mistakes don't need to define him.

126
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:05,015
Neither do yours.

127
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:07,309
[scoffs]

128
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:10,438
I should get going.
I don't wanna miss my window.

129
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:17,027
Really?
No, uh, "It's too dangerous, Karen"?

130
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:18,112
[chuckles]

131
00:12:19,363 --> 00:12:21,115
Clearly, you can handle yourself.

132
00:12:26,787 --> 00:12:29,832
[stammers] But, you know,
Karen, please, be careful.

133
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:34,462
Got it.

134
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,887
[police siren wails]

135
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:02,656
Detective Mahoney.

136
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:04,533
I see you're putting in
for early retirement.

137
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:08,370
No, sir, Mr. District Attorney.
There's someone who needs to talk to you.

138
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:10,956
Oh, hell.

139
00:13:16,754 --> 00:13:18,255
[Tower] You ever hear of a phone?

140
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:21,842
I'm as familiar with my phone
as you are with the "ignore call" button.

141
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:23,010
What do you want?

142
00:13:23,093 --> 00:13:25,846
Another viral video you can use
to campaign against me?

143
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,766
I want to make you an offer
that you won't want to refuse.

144
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:31,769
I can't wait.

145
00:13:31,852 --> 00:13:33,938
In exchange for an hour of your time,

146
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:36,482
I'll drop out of the race
and hand you the election.

147
00:13:36,565 --> 00:13:38,317
-What's the punch line?
-No punch line.

148
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:42,154
I'm just asking that you sit down with
Matt Murdock and me and a client of ours,

149
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:44,824
and just listen to what he has to say.

150
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:48,994
I do that, and you just drop out?

151
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:52,081
Uh-huh.

152
00:13:52,998 --> 00:13:55,000
You know,
I don't even pick up a book in the airport

153
00:13:55,084 --> 00:13:56,710
without reading the last page first?

154
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:59,296
I need to know what this meeting is about.

155
00:14:00,047 --> 00:14:01,006
[sighs]

156
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:04,260
-It's about Wilson Fisk.
-For the love of...

157
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:07,096
You need help, Nelson.
Get the hell out of my car.

158
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,639
Fisk is threatening my family.

159
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:12,434
He got them dirty, and now he's using them
as leverage against me.

160
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:20,818
So if you win the election...

161
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:25,614
and take my job,
Fisk will control New York's DA?

162
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:28,492
Right.

163
00:14:28,576 --> 00:14:32,788
So, honestly, I'm dropping out whether
you give me an hour of your time or not.

164
00:14:34,915 --> 00:14:36,625
But I'm asking you to anyway.

165
00:14:37,418 --> 00:14:38,919
You'll withdraw publicly?

166
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:40,880
And endorse you.

167
00:14:41,463 --> 00:14:44,466
Throw in an extra 15 minutes,
I'll even vote for you.

168
00:14:48,762 --> 00:14:50,097
[Matt] <i>You ready for this?</i>

169
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:52,224
Testifying is not gonna be easy.

170
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:56,645
I loved my job.

171
00:14:58,188 --> 00:15:00,107
And I loved being the good guy.

172
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:05,446
I want to be
on the right side of the line again.

173
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:06,363
[Matt chuckles]

174
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:09,658
You didn't love it enough to stop Fisk.

175
00:15:14,038 --> 00:15:16,540
Fisk knows how to make people vulnerable.

176
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:21,211
He got my sister-in-law's
health insurance canceled,

177
00:15:21,295 --> 00:15:23,547
left my family with bills to pay.
Bills that I had to--

178
00:15:23,631 --> 00:15:26,133
So you take a loan, you sell your house,
you figure it out.

179
00:15:26,216 --> 00:15:28,052
You don't allow yourself
to become an accessory.

180
00:15:28,135 --> 00:15:30,054
-It wasn't that easy--
-You backed his play, Ray.

181
00:15:30,137 --> 00:15:32,348
You moved him into his hotel,
even gave him his toys back.

182
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:34,099
He was giving information
that saved lives.

183
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:36,518
While he was taking lives.
While he was taking over the city!

184
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,854
What the hell are you doing?
I thought you were my lawyer!

185
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:42,232
I am your lawyer, but I can't help you if
you can't answer this one simple question.

186
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:45,611
Why didn't you blow the whistle when you
watched your boss murder an agent?

187
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:47,488
I don't know.

188
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:49,323
Or when you saw Dex walk in that church?

189
00:15:49,406 --> 00:15:52,409
You didn't say a goddamn word
when he murdered a priest.

190
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:54,036
-I don't know.
-Then why are we here?!

191
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:55,996
Because I took the damn bait!

192
00:16:02,419 --> 00:16:07,257
Because I didn't want my son to see me
as just an average federal employee.

193
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:13,597
I messed up.

194
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:17,476
I destroyed my life.

195
00:16:20,437 --> 00:16:21,814
My family's life.

196
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:29,154
And I would do anything
to take it all back again.

197
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:31,782
Good.

198
00:16:32,324 --> 00:16:35,202
You tell that to the DA,
and I can help you.

199
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:47,589
Blake Tower, FBI Special Agent Ray Nadeem.

200
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:48,882
We've met.

201
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:51,135
[Matt] Before we begin, some ground rules.

202
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:54,054
Our client will speak to you
under terms of use immunity.

203
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:56,015
He does not waive
his Fifth Amendment rights.

204
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:59,768
Special Agent, I should advise you
that Misters Nelson and Murdock

205
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:01,270
have their own agendas in this case.

206
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:04,189
Conflicts of interest are not something
you want in legal counsel.

207
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:08,610
I trust them. [Tower] Suit yourself.

208
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:14,783
Mr. Nelson played his biggest
and last card to get me here.

209
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:18,037
So, what are you going to tell me?

210
00:17:19,121 --> 00:17:21,790
He's going to tell you that Wilson Fisk
has had people murdered,

211
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:23,917
blackmailed
federal law enforcement personnel,

212
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,669
and is currently taxing
New York's criminals

213
00:17:25,753 --> 00:17:27,755
in exchange for protection
from prosecution.

214
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:29,882
And your client
has personally witnessed these acts?

215
00:17:29,965 --> 00:17:32,426
He did. And he's prepared to testify.

216
00:17:33,969 --> 00:17:36,013
[Tower] Now, before I agree to that,

217
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:38,974
Agent Nadeem,
why are you coming forward now?

218
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:44,897
I hurt people.

219
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:48,192
My pride hurt people.

220
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:52,112
And I need to make that right again.

221
00:17:53,989 --> 00:17:54,990
Okay.

222
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:59,369
I accept the terms of use immunity.

223
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:01,955
Tell me what you know.

224
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:10,881
[shudders]

225
00:18:14,009 --> 00:18:16,386
[door opens and closes]

226
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:27,564
Can I get you anything else, sir?

227
00:18:32,694 --> 00:18:36,782
I just wanted to say I'm sorry
about Karen Page.

228
00:18:37,741 --> 00:18:41,036
She would be dead
if Agent Nadeem hadn't interfered.

229
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,418
After everything you've done for me, I...

230
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:53,549
I just wanted to tell you
that I'll keep my word.

231
00:18:53,632 --> 00:18:56,051
I will find her, and when I do,
I am going--

232
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:57,344
No.

233
00:18:58,011 --> 00:19:00,222
This matter will be handled,
but not by you.

234
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:03,392
-I can handle Agent Nadeem.
-Do nothing.

235
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:08,230
It's clear that I have put
too great a burden on your shoulders.

236
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:16,655
[soft droning]

237
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:23,704
[Ray] <i>After the attack on my home...</i>

238
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:27,875
I secured my family
and came directly here.

239
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:33,255
-This is unbelievable.
-Believe it.

240
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:37,968
I can convene a special grand jury today.
Probably by 4:00 p.m.

241
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:39,803
Great. Our offer is straightforward.

242
00:19:39,887 --> 00:19:42,556
Agent Nadeem's testimony
in exchange for full immunity.

243
00:19:47,102 --> 00:19:50,647
He just confessed to being
an accessory in how many homicides?

244
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:52,983
Cases you would never make
in a million years

245
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:54,318
without our client's testimony.

246
00:19:54,401 --> 00:19:57,404
If this was a larceny case,
or corruption, maybe.

247
00:19:57,487 --> 00:20:00,991
But he's a federal law enforcement officer
that looked the other way

248
00:20:01,074 --> 00:20:03,702
while class A felonies,
homicides, were committed.

249
00:20:03,785 --> 00:20:06,872
Two men were murdered in front of him,
and he never said a damn word.

250
00:20:06,955 --> 00:20:09,249
He didn't say a thing,
because he was afraid for his family.

251
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:10,876
Fisk tried to kill them all last night,

252
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:13,879
and Agent Nadeem is here today,
telling you everything.

253
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:16,256
Can you say
you'd do the same thing, Mr. Tower?

254
00:20:17,841 --> 00:20:19,676
Our offer expires
when you walk out that door.

255
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,763
Full immunity, or we're advising
our client to run for his life.

256
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:26,767
Five years.

257
00:20:27,726 --> 00:20:29,269
-On each count.
-No.

258
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:33,023
-[Tower] You can't do murder and walk.
-[Foggy] Come on, Blake, no jail time.

259
00:20:33,106 --> 00:20:35,484
You'll be the DA
who took down Wilson Fisk,

260
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:38,487
and the next stop on the Tower train
is the governorship.

261
00:20:42,449 --> 00:20:45,202
Five years, on all counts.

262
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:46,370
Final offer.

263
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:49,081
Thank you for coming by, Mr. Tower.

264
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:56,463
Wait.

265
00:20:58,548 --> 00:20:59,633
He's right.

266
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:01,969
I did the crime.

267
00:21:05,472 --> 00:21:07,849
And I need to keep my family safe.

268
00:21:10,394 --> 00:21:11,561
I'll take it.

269
00:21:15,482 --> 00:21:16,525
It's okay.

270
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,486
I'm good with this.

271
00:21:22,197 --> 00:21:23,490
[Tower] Let me make a call.

272
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:25,325
[door opens]

273
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:27,911
[door closes]

274
00:21:28,495 --> 00:21:31,498
Sami, there's something
I need to talk to you about.

275
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:38,130
You might hear some stories about me,
some stuff that...

276
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:41,216
sounds like I did bad things.

277
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:47,306
No, I didn't do them.

278
00:21:49,516 --> 00:21:51,893
But I didn't stop them
from happening, either.

279
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:56,148
And that's just as bad.

280
00:21:57,441 --> 00:21:59,609
I was trying to keep
you and your mom safe.

281
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:03,488
That's all that matters to me.

282
00:22:04,239 --> 00:22:07,034
I don't care what people say about me,

283
00:22:07,576 --> 00:22:12,622
all I care about is...
what you say about me,

284
00:22:13,582 --> 00:22:16,126
and that you get to live
the life that you want.

285
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:17,961
I love you, kid.

286
00:22:18,045 --> 00:22:20,088
Hey. Feels good, right?

287
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:23,425
What? Letting Ray serve five years?

288
00:22:23,508 --> 00:22:26,386
Any other lawyers,
he would've gone away a lot longer.

289
00:22:28,096 --> 00:22:30,640
But I meant working together, you and me.

290
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:34,561
Doing what we're supposed to be doing
the way we're supposed to be doing it.

291
00:22:34,644 --> 00:22:37,272
Yeah... it felt good.

292
00:22:37,356 --> 00:22:38,607
Right?

293
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:42,652
I miss this, working together,
giving a shit about my clients.

294
00:22:42,736 --> 00:22:46,073
Not just billing midtown jackholes
in six-minute increments.

295
00:22:46,615 --> 00:22:48,533
Those jackholes pay well, though, huh?

296
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:50,202
What, are those new shoes?

297
00:22:51,036 --> 00:22:53,080
Seems like you
got used to the money, Nelson.

298
00:22:53,163 --> 00:22:54,581
So I'll get unused to it.

299
00:22:54,664 --> 00:22:56,291
We should do this again.

300
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:58,335
Don't get ahead of yourself.
We're not there yet.

301
00:22:58,418 --> 00:22:59,628
But we're getting there.

302
00:23:00,462 --> 00:23:01,671
[sighs]

303
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:31,701
Vanessa.

304
00:23:32,369 --> 00:23:35,497
I'm sorry, I overslept.
Long flights do me in.

305
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:39,751
I heard the shower.
I thought you might be famished.

306
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:43,171
-My favorite.
-Yes, I remember.

307
00:23:45,298 --> 00:23:46,425
[Vanessa chuckles]

308
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:54,891
More salt?

309
00:23:55,475 --> 00:23:56,685
It's perfect.

310
00:24:14,578 --> 00:24:16,455
Vanessa, something's bothering you.

311
00:24:18,874 --> 00:24:20,417
Please tell me what it is.

312
00:24:25,422 --> 00:24:26,339
[sighs]

313
00:24:26,423 --> 00:24:29,843
While I was away, I was always surrounded
by your bodyguards.

314
00:24:34,514 --> 00:24:36,308
"How are you, Ms. Marianna?"

315
00:24:37,434 --> 00:24:39,686
"How is your day going, Ms. Marianna?"

316
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:42,022
I was always "fine."

317
00:24:42,898 --> 00:24:46,401
The day was always "nice."

318
00:24:47,194 --> 00:24:52,491
One day, I, um, found myself
on the Nervión River in Bilbao.

319
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:54,743
Hundreds of people...

320
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:58,955
Tourists posed for pictures, held hands...

321
00:25:00,707 --> 00:25:02,876
kissed on the riverfront.

322
00:25:03,710 --> 00:25:06,838
I was surrounded by people...

323
00:25:09,382 --> 00:25:11,176
but I wasn't with them.

324
00:25:12,677 --> 00:25:14,012
I was lonely.

325
00:25:16,973 --> 00:25:19,559
Vanessa, we have both been lonely.

326
00:25:20,101 --> 00:25:21,311
And I still am.

327
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:29,277
I'm here, surrounded by your things,
your people, even you...

328
00:25:32,864 --> 00:25:35,450
but I still don't feel that I'm with you.

329
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:40,121
What can I do?

330
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:43,458
-I'll do anything. Please, tell me.
-[door opens]

331
00:25:43,542 --> 00:25:44,626
[Felix clears throat]

332
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:51,841
I am sorry to bother you, sir,
but I'm afraid this cannot wait.

333
00:25:53,051 --> 00:25:54,052
Not here.

334
00:25:59,307 --> 00:26:00,392
I have to...

335
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:06,189
Forgive me, please.

336
00:26:07,357 --> 00:26:08,525
[Vanessa] Of course.

337
00:26:19,494 --> 00:26:21,413
[Fisk] <i>Never in front of Vanessa.</i>

338
00:26:23,498 --> 00:26:24,624
Tell me.

339
00:26:24,708 --> 00:26:28,211
Agent Nadeem has not yet been located.

340
00:26:28,295 --> 00:26:29,796
But my source tells me

341
00:26:29,879 --> 00:26:33,717
that the state's grand jury
that was to be released this morning

342
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,260
has been held late.

343
00:26:35,343 --> 00:26:39,848
What's more, courthouse security
has been dramatically increased.

344
00:26:39,931 --> 00:26:41,558
These could be indications--

345
00:26:41,641 --> 00:26:43,810
Nadeem is intending to testify.

346
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:48,398
That could be problematic.

347
00:26:48,481 --> 00:26:50,442
Yes, it would, sir.

348
00:26:50,525 --> 00:26:54,195
What's unclear to me
is how you failed to kill him!

349
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:57,782
Daredevil interfered.

350
00:26:58,783 --> 00:27:01,202
The men responsible have been eliminated.

351
00:27:01,286 --> 00:27:05,498
However, the ultimate responsibility
does rest with me.

352
00:27:06,041 --> 00:27:10,462
If you would like my resignation,
I understand.

353
00:27:15,717 --> 00:27:17,052
You protected her...

354
00:27:19,387 --> 00:27:20,764
two years.

355
00:27:23,016 --> 00:27:25,352
You kept Vanessa safe when I couldn't.

356
00:27:27,187 --> 00:27:29,981
No, Felix. I want you to finish the job.

357
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:39,032
If you need assistance, call our friends.

358
00:27:44,996 --> 00:27:46,581
Do whatever it takes.

359
00:27:48,249 --> 00:27:50,168
I will not be indicted.

360
00:27:52,545 --> 00:27:54,255
Hey, Tommy, I'll have two--

361
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:57,425
Two knishes with extra sauerkraut
and extra mustard.

362
00:27:59,803 --> 00:28:01,054
It's 11:40. You're a creature of habit.

363
00:28:06,935 --> 00:28:07,769
[chuckles]

364
00:28:09,938 --> 00:28:12,232
This totally doesn't mean
that I forgive you, by the way.

365
00:28:12,315 --> 00:28:14,109
-I'm trying to keep a low profile.
-I'm sorry.

366
00:28:14,192 --> 00:28:16,069
You-know-who's people
are looking for me, so...

367
00:28:16,152 --> 00:28:17,696
Well, after what happened
at the church,

368
00:28:17,779 --> 00:28:20,198
so is every FBI agent
and reporter in the city.

369
00:28:21,449 --> 00:28:22,951
Uh, your knishes?

370
00:28:23,576 --> 00:28:24,953
Oh! Uh, here.

371
00:28:28,915 --> 00:28:31,084
So, um... are we doing this?

372
00:28:32,001 --> 00:28:36,214
If by "this" you mean
I tell you who Daredevil is, then no.

373
00:28:37,132 --> 00:28:40,677
What I can tell you is who attacked
the <i>Bulletin</i> in Daredevil's suit.

374
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:41,845
Do you have a name?

375
00:28:42,554 --> 00:28:43,847
Ben Poindexter.

376
00:28:44,681 --> 00:28:46,141
The FBI agent who saved Fisk.

377
00:28:46,224 --> 00:28:48,226
Yeah, well,
apparently he made a good impression,

378
00:28:48,309 --> 00:28:49,602
because he's working for him now.

379
00:28:49,686 --> 00:28:52,105
-And you can prove this how?
-I don't have to.

380
00:28:52,188 --> 00:28:54,482
In a couple of hours,
the head of Fisk's FBI detail

381
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:57,152
is going to testify to everything
in front of a grand jury.

382
00:28:57,235 --> 00:28:59,362
Ray Nadeem
is going to turn state's witness.

383
00:29:01,072 --> 00:29:02,365
-Wow.
-Yeah.

384
00:29:02,449 --> 00:29:04,409
It's a hell of an exclusive. Welcome back.

385
00:29:04,492 --> 00:29:07,454
No, see, actually,
it's not gonna be an exclusive.

386
00:29:08,663 --> 00:29:12,041
Come on, Ellison, this is...
This is bigger than just our newspaper.

387
00:29:12,125 --> 00:29:15,170
When Fisk had our offices attacked,
he was trying to silence the truth.

388
00:29:18,506 --> 00:29:19,716
God help me.

389
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:20,967
-[Karen sighs]
-[clears throat]

390
00:29:21,050 --> 00:29:24,053
Okay, so what is it, exactly,
that you want me to do?

391
00:29:24,137 --> 00:29:26,139
I need you to call a press conference.

392
00:29:26,806 --> 00:29:31,728
Just tell everyone
that Karen Page wants to make a statement.

393
00:29:46,659 --> 00:29:49,662
This is from Wilson.

394
00:29:52,749 --> 00:29:54,542
I was wondering where it had gone.

395
00:29:55,335 --> 00:29:57,253
Hey, we haven't formally met yet.

396
00:29:58,087 --> 00:30:00,173
I'm Agent Poindexter.

397
00:30:00,715 --> 00:30:01,716
Dex.

398
00:30:02,383 --> 00:30:07,972
If you need anything at all,
just think of me as the new James Wesley.

399
00:30:08,765 --> 00:30:09,974
Pleasure to meet you.

400
00:30:10,517 --> 00:30:11,851
Vanessa Marianna.

401
00:30:16,356 --> 00:30:17,482
[Vanessa sighs]

402
00:30:17,565 --> 00:30:21,236
I've always told Wilson
he has great taste in art.

403
00:30:24,322 --> 00:30:26,991
He does love to put
beautiful things on display.

404
00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:30,995
Where did you find it?

405
00:30:31,621 --> 00:30:35,291
Some lady had it.
Wilson couldn't get her to sell it.

406
00:30:36,251 --> 00:30:38,920
Well, that must have been
very disappointing for him.

407
00:30:39,921 --> 00:30:43,049
It's the painting in his collection
that means the most to us.

408
00:30:43,967 --> 00:30:45,301
I figured that...

409
00:30:45,885 --> 00:30:49,097
so I thought I'd ask her
just one last time.

410
00:31:00,567 --> 00:31:02,527
Thank you, Agent Poindexter.

411
00:31:03,862 --> 00:31:06,656
Perhaps you can arrange
to have it hung for us?

412
00:31:09,742 --> 00:31:11,494
It'd be my pleasure, ma'am.

413
00:31:13,913 --> 00:31:15,039
[Ray] What about Nelson?

414
00:31:15,623 --> 00:31:17,792
Foggy's ironing out some details
with the DA.

415
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:19,669
He's gonna meet us at the courthouse.

416
00:31:20,169 --> 00:31:22,297
-Then let's get this over with.
-Not that one. This one.

417
00:31:24,549 --> 00:31:25,550
[Ray] Really? [Matt] Hey.

418
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:32,473
Mahoney tell you this could get rough?

419
00:31:33,099 --> 00:31:35,602
He told me you're taking out Fisk.
That's all I need to hear.

420
00:31:36,185 --> 00:31:37,478
Courthouse. No stops.

421
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:54,162
[sirens wailing]

422
00:32:02,545 --> 00:32:04,088
I need to ask you something.

423
00:32:07,675 --> 00:32:10,219
You want to know about Daredevil. [sighs]

424
00:32:12,305 --> 00:32:17,560
I stepped off the path for a few weeks,
and it destroyed my life...

425
00:32:19,145 --> 00:32:23,149
But your life,
you step on and off all the time.

426
00:32:25,985 --> 00:32:27,820
It complicates my life, too.

427
00:32:29,781 --> 00:32:31,950
-Trying to have it both ways.
-Does it?

428
00:32:32,033 --> 00:32:35,244
I mean, your friends know who you are,
what you do.

429
00:32:35,328 --> 00:32:36,913
My life almost got them killed.

430
00:32:37,455 --> 00:32:38,748
And not for the first time.

431
00:32:40,124 --> 00:32:42,210
I don't see how I can have it both ways.

432
00:32:43,461 --> 00:32:44,754
But you already do.

433
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:49,968
I messed up,
and no matter what happens today...

434
00:32:51,427 --> 00:32:53,888
I don't know
if my wife's ever coming back.

435
00:32:56,557 --> 00:32:58,267
But your friends keep coming back.

436
00:32:59,143 --> 00:33:01,396
I mean, how do you hold onto them?

437
00:33:05,650 --> 00:33:06,776
It's not me.

438
00:33:08,403 --> 00:33:09,404
It's them.

439
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:13,866
[vehicles honking]

440
00:33:21,958 --> 00:33:24,002
[indistinct chatter]

441
00:33:26,254 --> 00:33:28,006
[horn honking]

442
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:31,050
[man 1] Light it up.

443
00:33:32,885 --> 00:33:34,929
[automatic gunfire]

444
00:33:35,013 --> 00:33:36,222
[screaming]

445
00:33:41,185 --> 00:33:43,104
[driver gasping]

446
00:33:43,187 --> 00:33:44,897
[Ray] Get us out of here!

447
00:33:44,981 --> 00:33:46,274
He's dead.

448
00:33:46,899 --> 00:33:47,984
Draw your weapon.

449
00:33:49,318 --> 00:33:50,778
There's a guy there.

450
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:52,030
I can't shoot blind. Anybody--

451
00:33:52,113 --> 00:33:54,157
They're reloading, Ray! Fire your weapon!

452
00:33:55,116 --> 00:33:56,034
[man 2 grunting] There.

453
00:33:58,369 --> 00:33:59,871
-[man 3 grunting]
-Through there.

454
00:34:00,413 --> 00:34:02,707
-You got him.
-Let's go.

455
00:34:02,790 --> 00:34:04,792
Wait! Ray! Wait!

456
00:34:11,674 --> 00:34:12,717
[grunting] Clear!

457
00:34:24,854 --> 00:34:26,939
-We stick together. Understand?
-I know what I'm doing.

458
00:34:27,023 --> 00:34:29,317
-I'll get us to the courthouse.
-Stop, Ray. Listen to me.

459
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:30,359
You need to trust me.

460
00:34:30,443 --> 00:34:33,029
You pretend to lead me,
but you do what I say.

461
00:34:34,947 --> 00:34:36,824
Stay down.
All right, there's two ahead of us.

462
00:34:44,248 --> 00:34:45,792
-[keys rattling]
-[alert beeping]

463
00:34:45,875 --> 00:34:48,920
[panting] All right. Up ahead,
there's a way out. This way.

464
00:34:52,799 --> 00:34:53,966
Two o'clock. Go.

465
00:35:04,310 --> 00:35:07,105
-[pop music playing over car stereo]
-[woman gasping]

466
00:35:16,322 --> 00:35:20,118
[men speaking indistinctly]

467
00:35:21,202 --> 00:35:22,912
Bus. Take the bus.

468
00:35:23,496 --> 00:35:24,497
Wait.

469
00:35:26,332 --> 00:35:28,584
-[men continue indistinctly]
-Okay, go.

470
00:35:33,673 --> 00:35:35,007
Sit down. Wait for my cue.

471
00:35:41,055 --> 00:35:42,098
Hello?

472
00:35:42,181 --> 00:35:45,059
Hello? What's... what's happening?

473
00:35:47,270 --> 00:35:48,271
Hello?

474
00:35:48,938 --> 00:35:50,439
Hello? Is anybody there? Hey-- [grunts]

475
00:35:58,364 --> 00:35:59,448
[Ray grunting]

476
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:17,717
[grunting]

477
00:36:24,807 --> 00:36:27,435
-Let's go. It's just up ahead.
-[panting]

478
00:36:30,479 --> 00:36:32,565
Oh, shit. It's a cab.

479
00:36:32,648 --> 00:36:33,941
I think I should drive.

480
00:36:34,025 --> 00:36:35,401
[alert beeping]

481
00:36:38,613 --> 00:36:40,198
[car engine starting]

482
00:36:46,996 --> 00:36:48,122
[Karen panting]

483
00:36:48,206 --> 00:36:49,624
Hey. Where are they?

484
00:36:49,707 --> 00:36:51,584
-Late. Why?
-There's been an attack.

485
00:36:51,667 --> 00:36:53,169
People got shot a few blocks from here.

486
00:36:53,252 --> 00:36:55,504
-Oh, shit.
-They're locking down the building.

487
00:36:55,588 --> 00:36:58,424
-I need to call my office.
-Hey. We're here.

488
00:36:58,925 --> 00:37:02,345
-[Tower] What the hell happened?
-Fisk knows he's going to testify.

489
00:37:02,428 --> 00:37:04,013
-Are you in any condition to?
-[panting]

490
00:37:04,096 --> 00:37:06,349
-Absolutely, yeah.
-Okay. Let's go.

491
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:08,184
Okay, here's the deal.

492
00:37:08,267 --> 00:37:11,354
After you testify, Tower will take you
for arraignment, then we'll bail you out.

493
00:37:11,437 --> 00:37:12,271
What about my family?

494
00:37:12,355 --> 00:37:14,857
Spoke with Seema. They'll be on
a flight to Delhi in the morning.

495
00:37:14,941 --> 00:37:18,444
It's not forever. Just until we get Fisk
put away. And you'll get to say goodbye.

496
00:37:18,903 --> 00:37:21,280
-I don't know how to thank you--
-Don't. Just go get Fisk.

497
00:37:28,454 --> 00:37:31,290
-You all set?
-Yeah, Ellison really delivered.

498
00:37:31,374 --> 00:37:32,792
Is it just me, or did our plan--

499
00:37:32,875 --> 00:37:35,419
-Foggy, I'm begging you, don't say it.
-But it feels good, right?

500
00:37:35,503 --> 00:37:38,589
The three of us working together
and saving the... Okay.

501
00:37:38,673 --> 00:37:40,424
Look, I gotta go, okay?

502
00:37:42,927 --> 00:37:43,928
[Matt] Oh, man.

503
00:37:45,012 --> 00:37:46,222
[exhales sharply]

504
00:37:49,475 --> 00:37:51,519
[bailiff] You do affirm that
all the testimony

505
00:37:51,602 --> 00:37:54,105
that you are about to give
in the case now before the court

506
00:37:54,188 --> 00:37:56,941
will be the truth, the whole truth,
and nothing but the truth?

507
00:37:57,608 --> 00:38:00,861
This you do affirm under the pains
and penalties of perjury?

508
00:38:07,994 --> 00:38:08,995
I do.

509
00:38:15,459 --> 00:38:16,961
-Hey.
-Hey.

510
00:38:17,545 --> 00:38:18,713
You ready for this?

511
00:38:19,422 --> 00:38:21,590
Uh, no. [breathes deeply]

512
00:38:21,674 --> 00:38:23,050
Okay, come on. Let's go.

513
00:38:30,182 --> 00:38:32,435
Hi, I'm Karen Page.
I'm here to make a statement.

514
00:38:32,518 --> 00:38:34,478
-Why didn't Daredevil kill you?
-Let her speak.

515
00:38:34,562 --> 00:38:36,105
We have all been lied to.

516
00:38:36,856 --> 00:38:38,524
All right? We've been manipulated

517
00:38:38,607 --> 00:38:40,901
by a sociopath
who doesn't care about the truth...

518
00:38:41,444 --> 00:38:44,405
or about who he hurts
or about anyone other than himself.

519
00:38:44,989 --> 00:38:49,952
Last night, Wilson Fisk tried to have me
killed because I know the truth.

520
00:38:55,041 --> 00:38:59,211
The man who was wearing the Daredevil suit
is not the real Daredevil.

521
00:38:59,295 --> 00:39:00,296
<i>He is an impostor</i>

522
00:39:00,379 --> 00:39:03,758
<i>who is helping Wilson Fisk take back</i>
<i>control of New York's criminal underworld.</i>

523
00:39:03,841 --> 00:39:05,843
<i>At this moment,</i>
<i>a grand jury is hearing testimony...</i>

524
00:39:05,926 --> 00:39:08,012
-You seeing this?
-[reporter 1] <i>...Fisk is involved?</i>

525
00:39:08,095 --> 00:39:10,723
[reporter 2] <i>Can you identify</i>
<i>this impostor? This fake Daredevil.</i>

526
00:39:10,806 --> 00:39:11,724
<i>Where did he come from?</i>

527
00:39:11,807 --> 00:39:14,560
[reporter 1] <i>Who's testifying</i>
<i>to the grand jury? Can you give us a name?</i>

528
00:39:19,982 --> 00:39:20,983
Okay.

529
00:39:21,525 --> 00:39:23,235
Your client was very convincing.

530
00:39:23,778 --> 00:39:25,529
Keep him here
until the indictment comes in.

531
00:39:25,613 --> 00:39:27,031
Don't worry. We'll hold up our end.

532
00:39:27,114 --> 00:39:30,034
-[Tower] Good. I'm counting on it.
-Thank you, sir.

533
00:39:31,494 --> 00:39:32,578
You okay?

534
00:39:34,246 --> 00:39:38,751
For a guy who's about to send
his family away and go to prison? [sighs]

535
00:39:38,834 --> 00:39:39,835
Yeah, I guess so.

536
00:39:40,503 --> 00:39:41,670
You did good, Ray.

537
00:39:42,671 --> 00:39:45,091
You heard everything through the wall,
didn't you?

538
00:39:46,050 --> 00:39:47,760
You know that's kind of creepy?

539
00:39:47,843 --> 00:39:48,719
Oh, he knows.

540
00:39:49,261 --> 00:39:51,180
I heard a man standing up to Fisk.

541
00:39:51,847 --> 00:39:53,516
Your son will hear the same thing.

542
00:39:54,433 --> 00:39:55,976
And it'll mean a lot to him.

543
00:39:57,061 --> 00:39:59,355
I didn't know if we could
get this done today, but we did.

544
00:39:59,438 --> 00:40:00,439
No... you did.

545
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:03,859
So, thank you.

546
00:40:06,654 --> 00:40:08,030
So, what now?

547
00:40:08,989 --> 00:40:12,660
Hopefully, you'll serve out your sentence
in a minimum security prison.

548
00:40:12,743 --> 00:40:14,495
-Can't be sure.
-[juror speaking indistinctly]

549
00:40:14,578 --> 00:40:15,996
Will I do the whole term?

550
00:40:16,497 --> 00:40:18,624
My guess is
you won't serve the whole five.

551
00:40:18,707 --> 00:40:21,168
Hopefully. Good behavior, you never know.

552
00:40:21,252 --> 00:40:26,465
[juror] Willie Young,
789 West 144th Street.

553
00:40:27,758 --> 00:40:31,262
Sara Torres, 612 East 78th Street.

554
00:40:31,345 --> 00:40:33,764
What the hell? That's my address.

555
00:40:33,848 --> 00:40:35,224
Holy shit.

556
00:40:35,307 --> 00:40:37,852
[juror] Tom McGuinness, 707 Lovell Ave.

557
00:40:37,935 --> 00:40:41,772
I'm sorry, they made me memorize them.

558
00:40:41,856 --> 00:40:44,400
[Foggy] So just take it day by day.
That's all you can...

559
00:40:44,483 --> 00:40:46,235
Oh, no.

560
00:40:46,777 --> 00:40:49,196
-Matt? What's wrong?
-[exhales sharply]

561
00:40:50,614 --> 00:40:51,740
The jurors.

562
00:40:53,159 --> 00:40:54,493
Fisk got to them.

563
00:40:56,036 --> 00:40:59,999
<i>At this time, the grand jury</i>
<i>has elected not to indict Wilson Fisk,</i>

564
00:41:00,082 --> 00:41:03,002
<i>but this office, under my leadership,</i>
<i>will pursue every lead,</i>

565
00:41:03,085 --> 00:41:06,172
<i>every piece of evidence that leads us</i>
<i>to uncovering the truth,</i>

566
00:41:06,255 --> 00:41:07,465
<i>wherever we may find it.</i>

567
00:41:07,548 --> 00:41:09,967
[news anchor] <i>We'll continue to cover</i>
<i>this breaking news story</i>

568
00:41:10,050 --> 00:41:11,343
<i>as events unfold.</i>

569
00:41:11,427 --> 00:41:13,846
Karen Page,
this all started with you, didn't it?

570
00:41:13,929 --> 00:41:15,306
"Started"? What do you mean?

571
00:41:15,389 --> 00:41:18,142
You leaked the grand jury story,
and it was all a lie.

572
00:41:18,225 --> 00:41:19,185
No, it's not a lie.

573
00:41:19,268 --> 00:41:22,021
Is it a desperate attempt to boost
readership for the failing<i> Bulletin?</i>

574
00:41:22,104 --> 00:41:23,981
Screw you, Jerry.
What's Fisk paying you, anyway?

575
00:41:24,064 --> 00:41:25,691
-Get out of here.
-[reporters clamoring]

576
00:41:25,774 --> 00:41:27,151
[Ray vomiting]

577
00:41:28,194 --> 00:41:30,070
[Matt] It's not gonna end this way, Ray.

578
00:41:31,614 --> 00:41:32,823
We're not gonna let it.

579
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:34,366
The system will work.

580
00:41:34,450 --> 00:41:35,451
[scoffs]

581
00:41:35,534 --> 00:41:36,744
You still believe that?

582
00:41:36,827 --> 00:41:39,330
We've been here before. We can fix this.

583
00:41:39,413 --> 00:41:42,291
Tower will impanel another grand jury
and try again.

584
00:41:42,374 --> 00:41:44,710
We're not done here. Right, Matt?

585
00:41:45,294 --> 00:41:46,712
I told you this would happen.

586
00:41:46,795 --> 00:41:48,881
-I need to know where you're going.
-Gonna find Tower.

587
00:41:48,964 --> 00:41:50,591
Make sure he tries again.

588
00:41:51,550 --> 00:41:53,219
-Right. Good.
-[door opens]

589
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:54,887
-[water running]
-[door closes]

590
00:41:54,970 --> 00:41:55,888
[Ray sighs]

591
00:41:55,971 --> 00:41:58,098
When he gets back,
we'll get you someplace safe.

592
00:41:58,182 --> 00:41:59,600
[panting]

593
00:42:00,518 --> 00:42:01,977
Fisk is unstoppable.

594
00:42:03,187 --> 00:42:05,314
My family's never going to be safe.

595
00:42:05,397 --> 00:42:06,982
Don't talk like that, Ray.

596
00:42:07,566 --> 00:42:08,651
I'm sorry.

597
00:42:13,572 --> 00:42:14,573
[Ray] No...

598
00:42:15,741 --> 00:42:16,909
I'm sorry.

599
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:30,965
How did this get here?

600
00:42:31,966 --> 00:42:35,010
A gift from Agent Poindexter.

601
00:42:35,094 --> 00:42:37,054
He persuaded the owner to part with it.

602
00:42:40,057 --> 00:42:41,100
Did he?

603
00:42:45,145 --> 00:42:48,315
I intended for the painting
to remain with her.

604
00:42:51,485 --> 00:42:55,322
He said to think of him
as the new James Wesley.

605
00:42:58,701 --> 00:42:59,952
-Is he?
-No.

606
00:43:02,871 --> 00:43:04,290
But he is useful.

607
00:43:12,339 --> 00:43:13,632
[Vanessa] Is he dangerous?

608
00:43:14,758 --> 00:43:16,677
Nothing to be concerned about.

609
00:43:19,054 --> 00:43:20,055
I'll handle it. How?

610
00:43:21,223 --> 00:43:22,891
-It's not important.
-It is to me.

611
00:43:25,853 --> 00:43:27,896
I think it's time we speak plainly.

612
00:43:28,522 --> 00:43:29,523
Speak honestly.

613
00:43:30,399 --> 00:43:32,151
I'm always honest with you.

614
00:43:33,152 --> 00:43:37,156
When I first met you,
I was fascinated by your strength.

615
00:43:38,449 --> 00:43:43,412
Your brutality so clear to me,
even as you hid it from me.

616
00:43:44,330 --> 00:43:48,042
I wanted to observe everything you did.

617
00:43:48,125 --> 00:43:50,169
And as I did, I fell in love with you.

618
00:43:51,754 --> 00:43:52,963
But this?

619
00:43:54,757 --> 00:43:56,675
If this is all we have...

620
00:43:57,718 --> 00:44:00,012
it will leave me lonely, Wilson. As lonely as I was in Spain.

621
00:44:04,683 --> 00:44:07,686
When you stopped your man
from speaking in front of me, I...

622
00:44:08,270 --> 00:44:12,024
I was reminded
that I am not a part of your life.

623
00:44:14,526 --> 00:44:17,321
Not fully, and so not at all.

624
00:44:19,448 --> 00:44:20,574
And this...

625
00:44:22,951 --> 00:44:25,996
I don't want to admire your world.

626
00:44:27,206 --> 00:44:30,834
I want to live inside of it with you.

627
00:44:31,418 --> 00:44:35,714
Vanessa, it's one thing to know my work,

628
00:44:36,757 --> 00:44:38,425
but it's another...

629
00:44:40,552 --> 00:44:42,221
to dirty your hands with it.

630
00:44:42,304 --> 00:44:45,140
My hands were never clean.

631
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:47,935
If you truly want me...

632
00:44:49,645 --> 00:44:51,480
share your life with me.

633
00:44:52,398 --> 00:44:53,816
Fully.

634
00:45:10,374 --> 00:45:12,751
Come with me, please.

635
00:46:35,167 --> 00:46:36,335
Hey, beautiful. It's me.

636
00:46:38,754 --> 00:46:39,797
I'm home.

637
00:46:45,761 --> 00:46:47,429
You remember our wedding vows?

638
00:46:51,266 --> 00:46:53,268
"I love you more than life itself."

639
00:46:55,479 --> 00:46:56,605
I still do.

640
00:46:58,816 --> 00:47:01,985
And, Sami, your name means "elevated."

641
00:47:03,403 --> 00:47:05,280
And that's what you did for me.

642
00:47:05,989 --> 00:47:09,952
Made my life better
in the most unexpected ways.

643
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:13,914
Elevate your mom now.

644
00:47:38,313 --> 00:47:39,815
You're watching everyone.

645
00:47:41,692 --> 00:47:43,110
Everyone I need to.

646
00:48:00,168 --> 00:48:02,129
An update, please, Mr. Manning.

647
00:48:02,212 --> 00:48:04,882
And speak freely.

648
00:48:07,175 --> 00:48:09,761
I will no longer
keep anything from Vanessa.

649
00:48:09,845 --> 00:48:11,138
Very good, sir.

650
00:48:11,972 --> 00:48:15,100
Agent Nadeem has been located.

651
00:48:15,183 --> 00:48:19,438
His testimony to the grand jury
remains sealed and inadmissible...

652
00:48:20,188 --> 00:48:21,899
but given its public nature,

653
00:48:21,982 --> 00:48:25,027
we should weigh the benefits
of keeping him alive.

654
00:48:25,110 --> 00:48:29,239
Force Nadeem to stand trial
for the murder of Agent Winn,

655
00:48:30,616 --> 00:48:34,244
turning the FBI against him
and discrediting him in the press.

656
00:48:35,162 --> 00:48:37,080
My thoughts exactly, sir.

657
00:48:38,916 --> 00:48:43,962
Wilson, what does Agent Nadeem
know about your business?

658
00:48:45,213 --> 00:48:47,549
A considerable amount.

659
00:48:47,633 --> 00:48:51,637
And is he determined to find ways
to hurt you? To hurt us?

660
00:48:54,640 --> 00:48:55,933
Yes.

661
00:48:56,808 --> 00:48:59,645
Don't you think it would be safer
to remove the threat?

662
00:49:03,065 --> 00:49:04,191
Yes, I do.

663
00:49:08,236 --> 00:49:13,533
If Agent Poindexter is useful,
perhaps he can help us with this problem.

664
00:49:17,287 --> 00:49:20,290
-You'll let him know, won't you?
-[Felix] Yes, ma'am.

665
00:49:57,911 --> 00:49:59,246
I hoped it'd be you.

666
00:50:00,831 --> 00:50:01,832
Hi, Ray.

667
00:50:05,585 --> 00:50:07,295
Come on inside. Let's talk.

668
00:50:09,548 --> 00:50:13,760
Come on, Dex. We both know
you're a better liar than that.

669
00:50:15,387 --> 00:50:16,805
You want a private place to kill me.

670
00:50:18,765 --> 00:50:21,768
You're in a tough spot, Ray. I get that.

671
00:50:23,228 --> 00:50:26,064
It sounds hard. Really hard.

672
00:50:27,858 --> 00:50:31,445
When he's done with you,
he'll bury you, too.

673
00:50:33,447 --> 00:50:35,282
You know that, right?

674
00:50:36,033 --> 00:50:37,409
I'm doing fine.

675
00:50:38,535 --> 00:50:41,204
And you would be, too,
if you hadn't opened your mouth.

676
00:50:43,790 --> 00:50:45,876
It's not too late
to turn things around, Dex.

677
00:50:47,794 --> 00:50:53,800
Fisk manipulated you, just like he did me
and Tammy and everyone else.

678
00:50:55,469 --> 00:50:57,429
I can help you cut a deal with the DA.

679
00:50:58,638 --> 00:51:01,683
We can take him down, you and me.

680
00:51:01,767 --> 00:51:06,313
Two federal agents... like we were before.

681
00:51:08,023 --> 00:51:09,191
[scoffs]

682
00:51:10,400 --> 00:51:12,319
No, that's not gonna happen, Ray.

683
00:51:13,570 --> 00:51:15,197
I'm more than a fed now.

684
00:51:16,114 --> 00:51:19,201
I feel more myself
than I have in my whole life.

685
00:51:20,202 --> 00:51:21,661
Fisk gave me that.

686
00:51:30,378 --> 00:51:34,132
As long as I'm alive, my family's at risk.

687
00:51:40,180 --> 00:51:41,431
Let's go, Ray.

688
00:51:43,558 --> 00:51:45,727
I'm not going anywhere with you, Dex.

689
00:51:47,771 --> 00:51:52,692
[sighs] Whatever you need to do...
you do it here.

690
00:51:55,487 --> 00:51:56,530
[gunshot]

691
00:51:58,448 --> 00:51:59,950
[dogs barking]

692
00:52:30,689 --> 00:52:31,815
Thanks, Brett.

693
00:52:32,607 --> 00:52:33,775
Yeah, okay.

694
00:52:47,247 --> 00:52:50,709
-Matt, please...
-No. We tried it your way.

695
00:52:52,085 --> 00:52:53,086
[door opens] [door slams]

